						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							My guess would be that if there are lots of living people around a zombie will get quickly distracted from what it's eating to move on to another victim, leaving the original victim mostly intact to rise again. However, if there are lots of zombies and very few living people around there won't be a new stimulus to distract the zombie away so they keep eating as long as they can.<br />
