							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Maledict</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?p=1785497#post1785497" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">It doesn't really matter. Every zombie film or game I have ever seen, be it Walking Dead, 28 days later, World War Z, Dead Rising, Last of Us has the same traits. You constantly see the zombies killing (and usually devouring) people - but somehow there's hundreds of them and they spread like wildfire. It's as if they take a good bite out of someone and then leave them along to become infected.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Hm, no. <div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px">
<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>Spoiler</b> for <i>For a lot of those titles</i>: <input type="button" value="Show" style="width:45px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != 'inline') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'inline'; this.value = 'Hide'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none';  this.value = 'Show'; }">
</div>
<div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;">
<div style="display: none;">
In TWD everyone is infected.  They become zombies because they already have the virus.  In that universe there is no question of why zombies keep occurring, it's how did everyone become infected in the first place.  In Romero's films the viewer is dropped in on an already occurring zombie apocalypse, there is an expectation that the zombies will die out shortly for the reasons you mention and also they are getting stomped by the local populace.  They never become hordes in his films.  In World War Z it's because of a Chinese virus and they reach a critical mass then are managed and killed off thanks to the Redeker Plan.  Humans likely would have died out if not for that (according to people in WWZ). 
</div>
