				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Zombies: how do they work?
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1785531">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Silverblade-T-E</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?p=1785527#post1785527" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Alikat<br />
and again, that's fantasy, how can you &quot;cure&quot; what is &quot;fantasy&quot;?<br />
I have no problem with the undead of D&amp;D, they make sen  ein their milieu, but NOT these pseuo-science fiction ones<br />
<br />
as said, if they live they can be easily killed, as even an M16 can literally chop a person up with enough rounds, never mind .50 cals or tank rounds etc!<br />
<br />
if they do not breath have blood pumping they are not alive that is NOT possible, that is *fantasy* only that way, fantasy, could they be the &quot;so hard ot kill&quot;<br />
except, again as said, if they are mutants like in Will Smith's &quot;I am legend&quot;, but in that case, they'd be something overtly &quot;different&quot;<br />
<br />
often wante t o write sicfi novel I've got idea for, where such was used as a specific bioweapon, turn enemy into night stalking ghouls, to destroy moral, but they don't spread the disease much, or it causes YOU more problems<br />
<br />
<br />
as for scifi I have no objection to say &quot;an alien virus&quot; that turns people into tough, cunning but mentally retarded mutations, &quot;ghouls&quot; not &quot;zombies&quot;<br />
things that hunt for food and still have enough minds to get water, use cunning tactics etc<br />
depending on how &quot;weird&quot; the alien virus is you could have variations, like the boomers and chokers from &quot;Left4Dead&quot;<br />
<br />
it's the central point of *plausibility* that absolutely kills most zombie films for me.<br />
Romero's early work it didn't matter too much, but as it goes on...no, either they are fantasy undead, or they are scifi and please keep it plausible if scifi<br />
<br />
undead = yes, faith (holy items), silver and other stuff would work on 'em because that's fantasy<br />
I get annoyed at writers too scared to accept such who will always use the same damn schtick: &quot;to use the enemies weapons on them!&quot; like in vampire films/books, making the hero partial vampire<br />
<br />
no, gimmie Van Helsing. if you are talking about supernatural stuff, then *faith is real*. deal with it, it's *fantasy* <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
and frankly from my experiences, &quot;supernatural&quot; stuff, whether it's real or just misread unusual phenomena or delusions, is a HELL of a lot more scary than things that you fear may just kill you <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
<br />
<img src="http://crypticrock.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/tumblr_m3vavitwPJ1rs6hqwo1_500.jpg" border="0" alt="" /><br />
<br />
<br />
PS Return of the Living Dead is a great film, but that's humour/horror :P</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>I watched 28 Days Later just now.  I agree that the zombies proposed are the most plausible I have seen so far, because they don't try to consume their victim, just barf and roll out, and they deteriorate over time.  I do not think that the disease would spread cross borders though.  The incubation period is too short for someone to travel across oceans undetected and start turning everyone into zombies after landing.<br />
<br />
There's nothing inherent in zombies that precludes them from being realistic in the sense that they have to obey normal human needs though.  The zombie bit would come from their increased aggressiveness and single minded pursuit, which just entails that they would also exhaust themselves much quicker than what is seen in TWD (they are observed as getting weaker over time) or 28 Days Later (same deal essentially) and whatever changes the infection would cause.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
